{"title":"Watch changes in index","tags":["open"],"date":"2009-11-19T03:40:31Z","author":" <simon.a.chiang@gmail.com>","type":"issue","content":"Indexes really need to be aware of where they last were and where the gitgo branch currently is.  For example:\r\n\r\n* run gitgo --branch a\r\n* reindex\r\n* run gitgo --branch b\r\n\r\nNow the index will be set to wherever a is at.  This should be picked up quite naturally if the index is watching for push/pull.","at":"e7652914295bbfc2b6a72882d30e04519a2ecc2f","state":"open"}